  <div id="contentcol"> <h1 class="set2-banr"><img src="/img/sections/teach.gif" alt="Teaching" width="480" height="32" /></h1>
<div id="pstrip" class="teach"></div>

    <div id="content">
      <div id="sidebar">
        <div id="infobox">
          <h3>Related information </h3>
          <p><a href="http://teaching.berkeley.edu/teach-net.html">Teach-Net</a>:
            An e-mail list-serv for instructors </p>
          <p><a href="http://slc.berkeley.edu/ucftr/index.htm">Undergraduate student instructors</a></p>
          <p><a href="/academics/dept/a.shtml">Academic
            departments A-Z</a></p>
          <p><a href="/academics/school.shtml">Schools and colleges
            A-Z </a></p>
          <p><a href="/research/index.shtml">Research at UC Berkeley</a></p>
          </div> <!-- end infobox -->
        <img src="/img/sidebar-pix/classrm-200x150.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="150" /> </div> 
      <!-- end #sidebar -->
      <a name="maincontent" id="maincontent"></a>
      <p><a href="http://teaching.berkeley.edu/">Teaching &amp; Learning</a>: The Office of Educational Development, under the oversight of the <a href="http://vpapf.chance.berkeley.edu/">Vice Provost for Teaching, Learning, Academic Planning and Facilities</a>, administers programs that encourage teaching excellence and innovation, support faculty in their teaching, and recognize faculty achievement in teaching. The office also serves as a link to other teaching and learning related programs and activities on campus.</p>
      <p><a href="https://sis.berkeley.edu/bearfactsfacstaff/secure/bfw_domain_menu">Bear
        Facts</a>: Website where faculty can access student
        information
        &mdash; including class lists and wait lists &mdash; and
        can enter and submit final course grades. For students,
        Bear Facts includes class schedules, grades, billing,
        and financial aid.</p>
      <p><a href="https://bspace.berkeley.edu/">bSpace</a>: A collaboration
        and learning environment for faculty, GSIs, and students.</p>
      <p><a href="/teach/res.shtml">Resources, tools, technology</a>:
        Links to key units that support teaching, technological resources,
        and  tools, and teaching assistance. </p>
      <p><a href="ops.shtml">Unique teaching opportunities</a>: American Cultures, the Freshman Seminar Program, Letters and Science Discovery Courses, the Undergraduate Research Apprentice Program, and OLLI.</p>
      <p><a href="/teach/award.shtml">Professional development, recognition,
        and  fellowships</a>:
        Opportunities for recognition &mdash; such as the <a href="http://teaching.berkeley.edu/dta.html">Distinguished
          Teaching Award</a> and the <a href="http://gsi.berkeley.edu/awards/ogsi.html">Outstanding
            GSI Award</a> &mdash; as well as pedagogical research
        grants for faculty and GSIs. Also
        includes seminars and events.</p>
      <p><a href="/teach/policy.shtml">Committees and policies</a>:
        Guidelines and oversight bodies on issues pertaining to
        teaching and instruction at UC Berkeley.</p>
    </div>
